MSNOISE STEPS

Hong-Mao Huang, Dec 5, 2025

REMEMBER TO MODIFY THE PARAMETERS OF EACH PYTHON CODE!!

1. Get the seismic waveforms, and place them in the Seimic_Data folder.

2. Run 01_seismic_data_formatted_for_MSNoise.py to produce daily waveforms.

3. Please note that seismic stations without N, E, or Z components (such as DAS), the 01 python code will force it to be as Z component automatically. The DAS data works, but other kinds of seismometers haven't been tested yet.

4. Run the command "msnoise db init" in this folder. Select [1] sqlite and no Table prefix (just press the enter key).  

5. Run 02_Data_Scan.py to set up the configuration for MSNoise.

6. Run the command "msnoise new_jobs --init"

7. Run the command "msnoise compute_cc"

8. Run the command "msnoise stack -r and then run "msnoise reset STACK", and finally run "msnoise stack -m"

9. Run the command "msnoise compute_mwcs"

10. Run the command "msnoise compute_dtt"

11. Run 03_Visualization_CC.py
